  Source:
    Title: Chuang-tse
    Chapter: XVIII
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Happy Death
---
Chuang-tse said, ‘Were I to prevail upon God to allow your body to be
bom again, and your bones and flesh to be renewed, so that you could
return to your parents, to your wife, and to the friends of your
youth, -- would you be willing?’

At this, the skull opened its eyes wide and knitted its brows and
said, ‘How should I cast aside happiness greater than that of a king,
and mingle once again in the toils and troubles of mortality?’
